The paper deals with detecting fraudulent activity in online marketplaces, which involves analyzing user behavior and transaction data. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks), or cs.DB (Databases). However, since the paper focuses on network analysis and indices, cs.SI is the most likely sub-category. The other sub-categories are also relevant because the paper deals with security and privacy issues in online transactions, as well as the social and societal implications of fraudulent activity.
